reviews.text: Service was personable with great recommendations.  Food was delicious - best portobello mushroom sandwich I've had in a long time! It was flavorful and juicy on a thick roll with some kind of slaw. The hot mess was equally enjoyable. The lemonade was fresh and homemade- not too sweet or tart. We will definitely be back!

Excellent in every way. The food is fresh, flavorful and delicious. Even better than I expected. I‚Äôve enjoyed 9 Miles East‚Äôs To Go boxes many times throughout the years but this was my first visit to their cafe. If I lived closer I‚Äôd be a true regular! Excited to try more of the menu on future visits - the pizzas that others were enjoying looked fantastic - and even more excited to have 9 Miles East cater my wedding this summer!! Very clear I made the right choice :) Thank you 9 Miles East team!
Cute cafe that serves breakfast and lunch. The food combinations are different. Despite how good the Hot Mess breakfast looked, it was missing something. Next time, I'll try the lunch.

Visited Saratoga springs for Labor Day weekend. We ate her three times and that‚Äôs coming from a couple of food snobs. It‚Äôs that good. Dinner one night, breakfast the next day and then ordered dinner for delivery the following night. Great spot. Local sourced food. Nice people who work there. Pizza was very good. Sourdough in many aspects of dishes. Coffee great. Breakfast killer. Great spot!

9 Miles East never disappoints! Anything we‚Äôve ordered there always meets our expectations. Whether it‚Äôs dine in or take out , it‚Äôs always delicious. Their dishes are always full of flavors using the best and cleanest ingredients! It‚Äôs in my opinion the best place to grab a quick bite to eat for breakfast, lunch or dinner! Staff is always welcoming and extra friendly. In my opinion , I consider to be in the top 10 best eats in Saratoga Springs/Wilton area

detailedReviews.text: One of Saratogas hidden gems.   Food is varied and delicious.    Pizzas are made with sourdough and give them a little something that makes them special.   Salads are unique and out of 5 ive tried so far, each one is delicious in its own way.  Their chia pudding is tasty, and the pot de creme is a must.  They even have fermented jalape√±o hot sauce which is amazingly good.  My favorite is the hummus.    To call it good is an understatement.    It's the best hummus I've ever had.    Pricing is on the higher side but its all fresh, local ingredients so with it in my opinion.  Highly recommended.

detailedReviews.author: Bridget and Claire
detailedReviews.text: 9 Miles East catered our wedding in a rural area outside of Albany, and so many wedding guests told us it was the best food they‚Äôd ever had at a wedding. Gordon was so helpful, kind, knowledgeable, and responsive throughout the process. The team at the event were wonderful and did an excellent job, the dinner went off without a hitch. Good food was one of our top priorities for our wedding, and 9 Miles East went above and beyond with the delicious spread of appetizers, sides, and mains, while still being a budget-friendly option. 9 Miles East was a great value, incredible quality food and drinks, and a joy to work with; my wife and I would recommend them in a heartbeat to any other couple looking for a fantastic wedding caterer.

detailedReviews.text:
9 miles east has become our go to for pizza in the area. The sourdough crust is one of the best we‚Äôve had and the indecision meal (which includes chicken with root mash, a salad, and dessert) is worth every cent. We‚Äôll frequently stop in for breakfast as well and are always extremely satisfied.

The service is standout as well. Gordon and his team always go out of their way for the customers. I made a big mistake in my order, and they did not hesitate to replace it and expedite the fix, even though it was completely my fault. Always a pleasure stopping in here and will be back many more times.
